div.p:
We were, of course, uncertain which way things were going, so naturally we wanted
                    reporting from various parts of China. Canton was reporting on South China;
                    Kunming was reporting on Southwest China; Chungking, of course, on West China;
                    Hangzhou on the vital Yangtze basin. Those were the main Consulates at the time.
                    So primarily, really, it was political observation.
